  "text": "Moreover, [CITATION_1] inspected the effect of CRM on consumer satisfaction in Jordanian banks. The study recommended that there is no statistical relationship between customer relationship management components and consumer satisfaction as a dependent variable. The statistical analysis uncovered that there is a significant relationship between (CRM components represented by service quality, employee's behavior, customer data base, solving customer problems, physical environment, and social network interaction) as independent variables and the dependent variable consumer satisfaction in the banking industry.",
